pr_title: [NEW] Add Event Auth, init home component
pr_body:
This PR adds a component for sign-up sign-in with the event.
Tasks accomplished in this PR:

- [x] Add a Login form to log in with the Open Event Server
- [x] Add the functions to send the correct format data to Open Event Server to handle creating a new user or logging into Open Event Server(OES), since the OES, expects the `POST` payload to be in a certain format.
- [x] Add an Event Home page that handles showing the login button.

Thank you!

pr_body:
This PR adds a new UI for the event mainstage page.

Tasks accomplished in this PR:

- [x] Create a new route for the event poster page using NextJS dynamic routes.
- [x] Use the dynamic routes `id` in an API call function to GET the event details using the `id`, which is the same as the `event_id` in the Open Event Server DB.
- [x] Add an Event Info Tab, which displays the event description and an Event organizer's logo at the bottom.
- [x] Add Event Sessions Tab, which would be used for showing the Event Speaker Sessions.
- [x] Add Speakers Tab, which displays all the info about the Speaker in a nice UI.
- [x] Add an Event Image Header which on the medium display screens shows the Event banner on the left column, and the Event Date and location in the right column.
- [x] Add Event Registration/Ticket information div, using the React Bootstrap Navbar and the Intersection Observer API.
- [x] Use Intersection Observer API to display the Event Ticket Details in different locations on the screen based on user scroll.
- [x] Make the page responsive on Mobile displays and large screens.
- [x] Use Media Queries to detect the breakdown points and accordingly use different Event Image Headers for Mobile and Medium screens.


Thank you!

Fixes #7

pr_title: [NEW]Add Auto Auth Onclick and basic SuperProfile integration
pr_body:
This PR adds support for one-click login, we are using the npm package [crypto-js](https://cryptojs.gitbook.io/docs/#hmac) for hashing and creating passwords. And Paraphrase is used here with HMAC256. 
This PR will also add and implement the validation based on User roles.

- [x] Add Basic Auto login
- [x] Improve the Login routes
- [x] Implement the User role basic
- [x] Advance the User roles
- [x] Future Fixes
- [x] Setup local fauna

Thank you!

Fixes: #16.

pr_body: This PR adds a dashboard menu for the admin users to maintain and add new Speakers. Tasks accomplished in the PR: - [x] Define the routes for the Admin Dashboard page. - [x] Link these routes to the top navbar links by modifying the Strapi init data JSON. - [x] Develop an Event List Component that fetches all the Events owned by the user authentication is done based on the `access_token` stored in Cookie, which is read and sent along as an auth header with the API calls to the Open Event Server(OES). - [x] Add the Edit button and preview button on the Event List items. - [x] Add component to fetch and display individual Event Speakers after clicking the Edit button on the Event list item. - [x] Add a Modal form to get the basic Speakers Details to be mutated in the Event Speakers. - [x] Add a function to send the data received from the From in a specific format to OES as required. - [x] Add API call functions to handle sending the POST requests. - [x] Add a Delete button to delete the Event Speakers. Thank you! Preview:

pr_body:
Changes in the PR:
1. Updates in the `superprofile/initFaunaOnce.sh`, which incorporates the docker container health status check, if the status is not `healthy` then it stops the further dependent script operations.
2. Changes the name of the file `superprofile/CLOUDREADME.md` to `superprofile/cloud/README.md`, since there were issues with keeping multiple `README`

Feedbacks are most welcomed. Thank you!

pr_body: Hello, This PR works on introducing a new UI for the Greenroom page (previously at `virtualconf/greenroom`) now at (`conferences/greenroom/1`). Changes are done (to be updated as we progress): - [x] Introduce a common background wrapper component to be used for both the mainstage and greenroom - [x] Remove unnecessary and confusing buttons - [x] Remove the current non-working chat component - [x] Placed a placeholder for the chat component - [x] Remove unnecessary CSS files - [x] Remove unnecessary Jitsi buttons - [x] Add required functionalities using Jitsi API (mic mute, camera mute, and device settings) - [x] Revamp Mainstage page UI - [x] Integrate Chat Component on both the Mainstage and Greenroom page - [x] Add the People tab (showing current joined speakers) on the Speaker Greenroom Page - [x] Add validation on mainstage page for verifying logged in user - [x] Improve the dummy auth to login as "Admin, Speaker, and Attendee" roles - [x] Add support for RC Auth. - [x] Make Pages responsive to smaller screens - [x] Refactor build errors using middlewares - [x] Refactor Dummy Auth Current roadblocks: - [x] External call to `toggleScreenShare` in jitsi is not working. Next to be implemented in another PR: - [ ] Add Streaming switches Some preview images, Screen Capture: Fixes: #12 Thank you!

pr_body:
This PR moves the less prioritized `.env.old` file to the `log` repository. Since git ignores the empty folders, there were two ways one was to add a `.gitkeep` file, but while looking further into it, this was not an ideal approach and might lead to repository issues.
And the other was to add a `README` or any other file to this folder so I moved the `.env.old` in here since it was not in use ATM, and was only there for reference.

Thank you!

pr_title: [NEW] Add a script to select and change port
pr_body:
Changes in the PR:

- [x] An script to select unused ports for NextJS and Strapi.
- [x] Improvement in fauna and OES scripts for better error handling and startup.
- [x] Start Strapi from the script using `&`
- [x] Start NextJS from the script
- [x] Update documentations

Known roadblocks:

- [x] Unable to start both the Strapi and NextJS using the same script since neither of them runs in the background (detached shell).

Thank you!
